    <abstract>The Archivision Architectural Image Collection, a collection of approximately 15,000 high resolution images, encompasses a variety of examples of the built environment including images of architecture, gardens and parks, public spaces, and cities from North America, Europe, and Asia. The creation dates of the works depicted span from ancient times to the late twentieth century, with a particularly strong emphasis on the Renaissance, Baroque, and Neoclassical styles. The collection is created and curated by Scott Gilchrist, photographer and architect.</abstract>
